jparsec.ephem

Enum EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM>
      • jparsec.ephem.EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM>
    Enclosing class:
    EphemerisElement

    public static enum EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM
extends java.lang.Enum<EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM>
    The set of available algorithms. JPL ephemerides requires the ephemerides files, most of which are available for JPARSEC in the 20th and 21st centuries. You can also use external files, with no date limitation for DE406 and DE422.

      • JPL_DE406

        public static final EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM JPL_DE406
        ID value for JPL DE406 ephemeris algorithm. Available from 1900 to 2100. If you want maximum precission you should consider using this formulae, since it has good time span, acceptable performance, and is the officially adopted by IAU. Available from 3000 B.C. to 3100 from external files.

      • JPL_DE405

        public static final EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM JPL_DE405
        ID value for JPL DE405 ephemeris algorithm. Available from 1940 to 2060 in JPARSEC, or from 1600 to 2200 from external files.

      • JPL_DE403

        public static final EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM JPL_DE403
        ID value for JPL DE403 ephemeris algorithm. Available from 1950 to 2050.

      • JPL_DE200

        public static final EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM JPL_DE200
        ID value for JPL DE200 ephemeris algorithm. Available from 1940 to 2060.

      • MOSHIER

        public static final EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM MOSHIER
        ID value for Moshier ephemeris algorithm. Good precission in ancient times for the planets (but not the Moon), but other algorithms are better for 20th and 21st centuries. You may consider using ELP2000 for the Moon instead of this, especially in ancient times, despite that ELP2000 has poor performance.

      • VSOP87_ELP2000ForMoon

        public static final EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM VSOP87_ELP2000ForMoon
        ID value for VSOP87 or ELP2000 ephemeris algorithm. Good set of algorithms for planets and the Moon, but Moshier offers better performance and precission in planets in ancient dates.

      • SERIES96_MOSHIERForMoon

        public static final EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM SERIES96_MOSHIERForMoon
        ID value for Series96 (20th and 21st centuries) or Moshier Moon ephemeris algorithm. You may consider using JPL DE406 instead.

      • NEWCOMB

        public static final EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM NEWCOMB
        ID value for Newcomb ephemeris algorithm. Target object should be the Sun.

      • ORBIT
